    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="414"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 (E. W.)/11–742: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Admiral <persName type="from">William D. Leahy</persName>,
                        Chief of Staff to the Commander in Chief of the Army and Navy, to the Consul
                        General at Algiers (<persName type="to">Cole</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="16" xml:id="d414fn16">Copy supplied by the Office of the Secretary of
                        Defense under cover of letter of September 7, 1960.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-31">October 31,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. M–26. For Murphy. Please advise Flagpole that we consider it highly desirable
                    that French commanders be given instructions on D day that incidents on the part
                    of the Spanish, however provocative, should not be permitted to lead to
                    retaliatory action on the part of the French until after the consolidation of
                    the American forces on shore.</p>
                <p>Eisenhower is requesting British to make similar representations to France on D
                    day.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
